## ðŸ§ª 4. Static Analysis with Husky + Lint Staged

### Configure Husky

```bash
pnpm exec husky init
```

Add to `package.json`:

```json
"scripts": {
    "prepare": "husky",
    "test": "pnpm -r test:unit",
    "lint": "pnpm -r lint"
},
```

> This auto-generates `.husky/` hooks and keeps them in sync

---

### Add lint-staged

```bash
pnpm add -w -D lint-staged sort-package-json
```

Create `.lintstagedrc.js` in `apps/web` and `services/hello-service`:

```js
export default {
  "*.{ts,tsx,js,vue}": ["pnpm format", "pnpm lint"],
  "*.{json,yml,yaml,md}": ["pnpm format"],
  "**/package.json": ["pnpm sort-package-json"],
};
```

Add lint-staged to ./.husky/pre-commit:

```
pnpm exec lint-staged
git update-index --again
pnpm test
```

### vscode setup

Update `.vscode/settings.json`:

```json
{
  // ...
  "eslint.useFlatConfig": true,
  "eslint.workingDirectories": [
    { "pattern": "./services/*", "changeProcessCWD": true },
    { "pattern": "./apps/*", "changeProcessCWD": true }
  ],
  "eslint.options": {
    "overrideConfigFile": "./eslint.config.cjs"
  }
}
```

